The commands used for viewing running processes and their memory or CPU usage are :

> adb shell ps : This shows a static list of processes without CPU or memory usage.
> adb shell top : This shows a real-time list of running processes with CPU and memory usage.
> adb shell dumpsys meminfo : This gives the detailed memory usage of all processes.
> adb shell dumpsys cpuinfo : This shows the CPU usage of all processes.
